io.openmessaging

Interface ResourceManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ServiceLifecycle

    public interface ResourceManager
extends ServiceLifecycle
    The ResourceManager is responsible for providing a unified interface of resource management, allows the user to manage the topic, queue, namespace resources.

    Create, fetch, update and destroy are the four basic functions of ResourceManager.

    And the ResourceManager also supports fetch and update resource attributes dynamically.

    The attributes of consumer and producer also are treated as Resource. ResourceManager allows the user to fetch producer and consumer list in a specified topic or queue, and update their resource attributes dynamically.

    MessagingAccessPoint.getResourceManager() is the unique method to obtain a ResourceManager instance, any changes made by this instance will reflect to the message-oriented middleware (MOM) or other product behind the MessagingAccessPoint.

    Since:
    OMS 1.0
    Version:
    OMS 1.0
    Author:
    vintagewang@apache.org, yukon@apache.org

      • getConsumerProperties

        KeyValue getConsumerProperties(String consumerId)
                               throws OMSResourceNotExistException
        Returns the attributes of the specified consumer instance with the given consumer id. If no such consumer id exists, OMSResourceNotExistException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        consumerId - the unique consumer id for a consumer instance
        Returns:
        the attributes of the matching consumer instance
        Throws:
        OMSResourceNotExistException - if the specified consumer is not exists

      • setConsumerProperties

        void setConsumerProperties(String consumerId,
                         KeyValue properties)
                           throws OMSResourceNotExistException
        Sets the consumer attributes to the specified consumer instance.

        The new KeyValue becomes the current set of consumer attributes, and the getConsumerProperties(String) will observe this change soon. If the argument is null, then the current set of consumer attributes will stay the same.

        Parameters:
        consumerId - the specified consumer id
        properties - the new consumer attributes
        Throws:
        OMSResourceNotExistException - if the specified consumer is not exists

      • updateMessage

        void updateMessage(String messageId,
                 KeyValue headers)
        Updates the MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys of specified message, which may be stored by MOM server already.

        Only below message sysHeaders allow to be updated:

        • MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys.Priority
        • MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys.ScheduleExpression
        • MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys.StartTime
        • MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys.StopTime
        • MessageHeaderBuiltinKeys.Timeout
        Parameters:
        messageId - the message to be updated
        headers - the message sysHeaders to be updated
